stfeeding%2C%20I've%20experienced%20a%20lot%20of%20mental-health%20changes.%20For%20example%2C%20I've%20become%20incredibly%20superstitious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20superstitions%20started%20when%20my%20daughter's%20sleep%20regression%20resolved%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20started%20in%20the%20past%20few%20months.%20My%20partner%20and%20I%20had%20been%20dealing%20with%20some%20tough%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Ffour-months-sleep-regression%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esleep%20regressions%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20our%20baby.%20When%20she%20finally%20started%20sleeping%20through%20the%20night%20again%2C%20I%20was%20terrified%20she'd%20start%20regressing%20again.%20Out%20of%20superstition%2C%20I%20refused%20to%20admit%20out%20loud%20that%20the%20issue%20had%20resolved%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20friends%20or%20family%20members%20asked%20us%20about%20her%20sleep%2C%20I'd%20change%20the%20subject.%20If%20my%20husband%20tried%20to%20tell%20them%20she'd%20slept%2012%20hours%2C%20I'd%20nudge%20him%20and%20awkwardly%20ask%20him%20to%20stop%20responding.%20If%20he%20even%20dared%20to%20casually%20tell%20me%20how%20happy%20he%20was%20that%20we%20were%20snoozing%20through%20the%20night%2C%20I'd%20cut%20him%20off%20and%20get%20hysterical.%20I%20found%20myself%20having%20this%20deep%20underlying%20feeling%20that%20if%20we%20talked%20about%20how%20well%20we%20were%20sleeping%2C%20we'd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-origin-people-superstitions-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejinx%20the%20whole%20thing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20go%20back%20to%20waking%20up%20seven%20times%20a%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20realized%20I%20was%20cutting%20him%20off%20during%20these%20conversations%2C%20he%20would%20pause%20and%20later%20ask%20me%20if%20I%20was%20OK.%20I%20told%20him%20I%20was%20going%20through%20a%20challenging%20time%20and%20didn't%20want%20to%20have%20sleep%20conversations%20with%20anyone.%20When%20friends%20and%20family%20caught%20on%20to%20my%20awkwardness%2C%20I%20bluntly%20told%20them%20about%20my%20superstition.%20But%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20people%20around%20me%20would%20laugh%20at%20this%20superstitious%20behavior%3B%20they%20didn't%20realize%20how%20much%20it%20was%20affecting%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESoon%20I%20was%20superstitious%20about%20talking%20about%20her%20at%20all%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%20it%20popped%20up%20just%20in%20conversations%20about%20sleep%2C%20but%20soon%20whenever%20someone%20asked%20how%20she%20was%20doing%2C%20I'd%20say%20she%20was%20doing%20well%20and%20put%20an%20end%20to%20follow-up%20questions.%20My%20superstitious%20mindset%20was%20bleeding%20into%20every%20aspect%20of%20my%20life.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20talk%20about%20her%20health%2C%20mood%2C%20or%20feeding%20schedule%20because%20I%20was%20convinced%20that%20doing%20so%20would%20lead%20to%20some%20sort%20of%20disaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20to%20feel%20intense%20pressure%20that%20if%20one%20little%20thing%20was%20shared%20with%20someone%20about%20my%20baby%2C%20our%20entire%20world%20would%20negatively%20change.%20I%20was%20starting%20to%20isolate%20myself%20from%20friends%20and%20family%2C%20which%20wasn't%20a%20good%20way%20to%20live%20life%20as%20a%20new%20mom%20who%20desperately%20needed%20community%20and%20people%20around%20me.%20I%20decided%20to%20seek%20help%20and%20met%20with%20Kayla%20Estenson%20Williams%2C%20a%20licensed%20therapist%20who%20specializes%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouples-therapy-before-after-baby-giving-birth-conflict-resolution-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epostpartum%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20what%20was%20happening%20and%20some%20steps%20I%20could%20take%20to%20help%20me%20overcome%20my%20superstitious%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20talked%20with%20a%20therapist%20and%20learned%20some%20tools%20to%20cope%20with%20my%20superstitions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20feel%20sad%20when%20I'm%20having%20these%20intense%20superstitious%20moments%20because%20I%20don't%20feel%20like%20my%20old%20self%2C%20who%20would've%20been%20able%20to%20laugh%20off%20these%20intrusive%20thoughts%20and%20move%20on.%20Williams%20said%20it's%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20after%20birth%20a%20person%20experiences%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpostpartum-depression-therapist-most-helpful-tips-new-mom-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edrastic%20change%20in%20their%20hormones%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20hormone%20changes%20are%20designed%20to%20make%20us%20feel%20more%20connected%20to%20our%20baby%2C%20keep%20them%20safe%2C%20and%20be%20overly%20cautious%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20our%20brains%20and%20nervous%20system%20were%20designed%20to%20live%20in%20a%20world%20that's%20different%20from%20our%20world%20today%2C%20where%20we%20don't%20have%20the%20same%20type%20of%20dangers.%20Yet%20our%20hormones%20are%20telling%20us%20to%20be%20on%20high%20alert.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20Williams%20I'd%20experienced%20anxiety%20and%20depression%20in%20the%20past%20but%20found%20myself%20able%20to%20handle%20those%20conditions%20a%20lot%20better%20than%20I%20was%20dealing%20with%20things%20now.%20She%20explained%20that%20even%20if%20someone's%20familiar%20with%20a%20mental-health%20issue%20and%20has%20found%20ways%20in%20the%20past%20to%20deal%20with%20it%2C%20it%20might%20show%20up%20differently%20postpartum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20through%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouples-therapy-before-after-baby-giving-birth-conflict-resolution-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emajor%20transition%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20when%20you%20add%20in%20the%20hormone%20shifts%2C%20everything%20might%20feel%20more%20intense%20than%20it%20did%20in%20the%20past%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BOld%20coping%20skills%20might%20not%20work%20like%20they%20used%20to%2C%20and%20that's%20a%20good%20sign%20you%20might%20need%20new%20ways%20to%20help%20you%20get%20through%20what%20you're%20experiencing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20learned%20that%20being%20superstitious%20may%20be%20a%20sign%20of%20postpartum%20OCD%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20shared%20my%20superstition%20struggles%20and%20asked%20her%20why%20I%20was%20feeling%20so%20scared%20to%20have%20conversations%20about%20my%20baby%20with%20other%20people%20or%20say%20positive%20things%20out%20loud.%20She%20told%20me%20that%20being%20superstitious%20could%20be%20a%20part%20of%20postpartum%20OCD.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20having%20these%20obsessive%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiagnosed-ocd-intrusive-thoughts-of-hurting-people-scared-me-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eintrusive%20thoughts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20pairing%20them%20with%20compulsive%20behaviors%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20telling%20yourself%20that%20speaking%20about%20the%20baby%20will%20impact%20the%20baby%20in%20a%20negative%20way%2C%20and%20that's%20leading%20you%20to%20avoid%20conversation%20with%20people%20around%20these%20topics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20asked%20her%20if%20my%20intense%20superstitious%20mindset%20was%20normal%2C%20she%20said%20that%20even%20though%20it%20might%20be%20common%20for%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Focd-treatment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexperiencing%20postpartum%20OCD%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20still%20shouldn't%20be%20ignored.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20other%20parents%20around%20you%20are%20admitting%20to%20feeling%20the%20same%20type%20of%20things%2C%20if%20you're%20having%20intrusive%20thoughts%2C%20experiencing%20mental-health%20changes%2C%20or%20not%20feeling%20like%20yourself%2C%20you%20should%20get%20the%20support%20that%20you%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENow%20I%20open%20up%20to%20people%20about%20what's%20going%20on%20at%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20recommended%20that%20when%20I%20feel%20myself%20giving%20into%20that%20superstition%20I%20step%20back%20and%20try%20something%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAsk%20yourself%20if%20this%20truly%20makes%20sense%20and%20what%20it%20is%20that%20you're%20really%20feeling%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThink%20about%20if%20your%20actions%20are%20appropriate%20or%20even%20helpful%20for%20what%20you're%20needing%20at%20that%20moment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20advice%20helped%20me%20revamp%20how%20I%20approach%20these%20types%20of%20conversations%20that%20make%20me%20uneasy.%20Instead%20of%20shutting%20people%20down%20when%20they%20ask%20me%20a%20question%20about%20my%20baby's%20sleep%2C%20I%20share%20the%20truth.%20I've%20started%20opening%20up%20about%20what%20we're%20going%20through%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20was%20hard%20to%20do%20at%20first%2C%20and%20I%20was%20still%20nervous%20that%20what%20I'd%20say%20would%20jinx%20my%20sleep%2C%20I%20noticed%20the%20conversations%20I%20was%20having%20didn't%20directly%20affect%20my%20life%20at%20home%2C%20and%20it%20became%20easier%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20transparent%20with%20people%20instead%20of%20changing%20the%20subject%20has%20helped%20more%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-post-partum-anxiety-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderstand%20the%20anxiety%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20have%20around%20this%20topic.%20It's%20also%20helped%20me%20approach%20these%20conversations%20more%20directly%20and%20calmly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI'm%20also%20working%20on%20shifting%20how%20I%20respond%20to%20my%20intrusive%20thoughts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20worked%20on%20figuring%20out%20ways%20to%20respond%20to%20myself%20when%20I%20have%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-have-relationship-ocd-heres-how-i-deal-with-it-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eintrusive%20thoughts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20recommended%20that%20instead%20of%20quickly%20shutting%20down%20I%20ground%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAffirm%20to%20yourself%20that%20sleep%20for%20babies%20is%20tough%20and%20there%20will%20be%20ups%20and%20downs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20that%20is%20out%20of%20your%20control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20me%20that%20finding%20affirmations%2C%20or%20gentle%20reminders%2C%20can%20provide%20space%20to%20navigate%20challenges%20as%20they%20pop%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20created%20a%20list%20of%20affirmations%20for%20myself%20to%20counteract%20my%20superstitions.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20tell%20myself%20that%20I%20know%20my%20baby's%20sleep%20patterns%20are%20based%20on%20a%20lot%20of%20factors%20and%20that%20I'm%20doing%20what%20I%20can%20to%20help%20the%20situation.%20I%20practiced%20saying%20these%20a%20few%20times%20a%20day%2C%20and%20it%20did%20make%20me%20feel%20less%20anxious%2C%20especially%20when%20I%20started%20giving%20more-truthful%20updates%20to%20friends%20and%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhen%20I'm%20starting%20to%20doubt%20myself%2C%20I%20remind%20myself%20of%20the%20facts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20trying%20out%20a%20few%20of%20these%20things%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I'd%20jinxed%20the%20situation.%20Once%20I%20was%20telling%20a%20neighbor%20about%20how%20great%20my%20baby%20had%20been%20sleeping%3B%20that%20night%20she%20woke%20up%20five%20times.%20I%20told%20Williams%20I%20couldn't%20help%20wanting%20to%20run%20back%20to%20my%20superstitious%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20reminded%20me%20that%20some%20of%20our%20fears%20are%20going%20to%20happen%20and%20that%20it%20can%20feel%20like%20we're%20being%20proved%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20recommend%20reading%20and%20wri