20you%20and%20deleted%20all%20the%20blogs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20gutted.%20Of%20course%2C%20I%20%3Cem%3Eknew%3C%2Fem%3E%20they%20were%20bad.%20The%20client's%20entire%20website%20was%20pure%20cheese.%20I%20gave%20her%20what%20I%20thought%20she%20wanted%20and%20then%20asked%20for%20edits%20like%20always.%20Because%20the%20client%20and%20my%20former%20business%20partner%20were%20friends%2C%20the%20client%20shared%20the%20dirt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20telling%20me%20all%20the%20gory%20details%2C%20however%2C%20my%20former%20partner%20begged%20me%20not%20to%20let%20the%20client%20know%20she%20had%20spilled%2C%20lest%20she%20seem%20unprofessional.%20Nearly%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20not%20a%20single%20week%20goes%20by%20that%20I%20don't%20think%20about%20that%20conversation%20and%20being%20ditched%20by%20someone%20who%20meant%20so%20much%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESomehow%2C%20she%20still%20wanted%20to%20be%20friends%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-friend-ended-friendship-no-reason-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebusiness%20breakup%3C%2Fa%3E%20only%20pertained%20to%20the%20professional%20part%20of%20our%20relationship.%20She%20still%20wanted%20to%20be%20besties.%20She%20wanted%20to%20turn%20back%20the%20clock%20to%20how%20it%20was%20when%20we%20were%20just%20great%20friends.%20To%20her%2C%20working%20together%20and%20being%20friends%20were%20two%20separate%20boxes.%20She%20could%20check%20one%20without%20checking%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20no%20such%20filter.%20It's%20like%20when%20friends%20become%20a%20romantic%20couple%20and%20can%20never%20take%20it%20back.%20For%20me%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20every%20time%20I%20saw%20her%20I'd%20be%20reminded%20of%20how%20inferior%20she%20believed%20me%20to%20be.%20How%20could%20I%20be%20friends%20with%20someone%20who%20thought%20I%20was%20unskilled%2C%20terrible%20at%20my%20job%2C%20and%20lacked%20talent%3F%20Even%20if%20I%20was%20able%20to%20block%20out%20that%20pain%2C%20would%20we%20just%20never%20talk%20about%20our%20respective%20jobs%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20I%20didn't%20want%20someone%20in%20my%20life%20who%20would%20degrade%20me%2C%20tally%20up%20%26quot%3Bmistakes%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20address%20them%2C%20and%20email%20a%20list%20of%20insults%20then%20ignore%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20after%20that%20phone%20call%2C%20I%20decided%20we%20wouldn't%20be%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20decade%20later%2C%20I%20now%20see%20we%20were%20just%20different%20people%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20saw%20many%20things%20differently%2C%20and%20work%20was%20just%20one%20of%20them.%20She%20just%20had%20the%20wherewithal%20to%20rip%20the%20Band-Aid%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20more%20drive.%20She%20wanted%20to%20work%20with%20software%20platforms%2C%20to%20dive%20into%20the%20tech%20side%2C%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-pitch-yourself-as-speaker-for-industry-events-conferences-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espeak%20at%20conferences%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20to%20become%20a%20one-woman%20show.%20And%20me%3F%20I%20wanted%20to%20write.%20I%20wanted%20to%20tell%20people's%20stories%20in%20print%2C%20talk%20about%20their%20services%20online%2C%20find%20creative%20solutions%20through%20words%2C%20and%20work%20with%20a%20community%20of%20cheerleaders%20%E2%80%94%20where%20everyone%20provides%20a%20step%20so%20we%20all%20get%20to%20the%20top.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20since%20leaned%20into%20my%20strengths%20and%20found%20people%20who%20support%20my%20skill%20set%20by%20hiring%20me%20for%20content%20or%20design%20projects%2C%20not%20stats%20and%20code.%20I%20now%20work%20with%20people%20to%20discover%20their%20goals.%20I'm%20not%20trying%20to%20beat%20the%20competition%20and%20climb%20to%20the%20top.%3C%2Fp%3E%3