0gentrification%20has%20taken%20a%20toll%20on%20the%20local%20population.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20says%20Americans%20moving%20to%20Mexico%20need%20to%20stop%20staying%20in%20older%20Airbnb%20units%20among%20other%20things.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jeremy%20Albelda%2C%20a%2036-year-old%20entrepreneur%20living%20in%20Mexico%20City.%20It's%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20Philadelphia%20and%20moved%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Factivities-tourists-cant-miss-in-mexico-city-cdmx-local-tips-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoma%20Norte%2C%20Mexico%20City%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202015.%20My%20mom%20grew%20up%20in%20Mexico%20so%20I%20had%20always%20considered%20living%20there.%20I%20visited%20San%20Miguel%2C%20the%20expat%20community%20where%20she%20was%20raised%2C%20in%202009%20during%20my%20college%20winter%20break.%20At%20that%20moment%2C%20I%20knew%20I'd%20be%20living%20in%20Mexico%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20living%20in%20Mexico%2C%20I%20did%20content%20writing%20and%20worked%20in%20marketing.%20Then%2C%20I%20opened%20a%20British-themed%20pub%20and%20got%20involved%20in%20more%20restaurants%20and%20real%20estate%20there.%20After%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20things%20changed.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20appeared%20to%20be%20an%20influx%20of%20mostly%20white%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmexico-most-popular-country-americans-moving-abroad-migration-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmericans%20moving%20into%20Mexico%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2Fm7bgv8%2Fdigital-nomads-work-from-home-gentrification%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20exponential%20gentrification%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20taken%20a%20toll%20on%20the%20local%20population.%20Here%20are%20some%20things%20that%20other%20Americans%20moving%20to%20Mexico%20should%20stop%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Stop%20speaking%20English%20to%20locals%20right%20away%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20many%20locals%20speak%20English%20in%20the%20gentrified%20parts%20of%20Mexico%2C%20it's%20still%20polite%20to%20begin%20talking%20to%20them%20in%20Spanish%20before%20switching%20to%20English.%20This%20shows%20that%20you're%20trying%20to%20learn%20the%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20try%20not%20to%20speak%20English%20on%20the%20street%20or%20loudly%20at%20restaurants.%20You%20need%20to%20learn%20the%20language%20or%20at%20least%20a%20few%20phrases%20before%20you%20move%20here.%20I%20have%20friends%20who've%20been%20here%20for%20years%20and%20don't%20speak%20Spanish%20which%20is%20pretty%20bogus.%20I%20find%20it%20offensive%20and%20culturally%20insensitive.%20Being%20polite%20goes%20a%20long%20way%20and%20starting%20any%20verbal%20interaction%20with%20at%20least%20an%20%26quot%3Bhola%26quot%3B%20is%20expected%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flearn-spanish-2014-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMake%20an%20effort%20to%20learn%20Spanish%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20you'll%20help%20improve%20the%20overall%20image%20of%20remote%20workers%20and%20tourists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Stop%20staying%20in%20older%20Airbnb%20units%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOlder%20Airbnb%20unit%20owners%20usually%20displaced%20a%20local%20resident%20to%20turn%20it%20into%20an%20Airbnb.%20The%20newer%20Airbnb%20units%20are%20built%20with%20tourists%20in%20mind%20so%20it's%20less%20likely%20that%20a%20local%20resident%20was%20kicked%20out%20or%20priced%20out%20of%20that%20space.%20Recently%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmexlaw.com%2Fformalized-tax-collection-airbnb-quintana-roo%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMexican%20government%20partnered%20with%20Airbnb%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20regulations%20and%20new%20tax%20laws%20to%20promote%20more%20Airbnbs%20and%20help%20tourism%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirbnb%20prices%20have%20gone%20up%20along%20with%20other%20real%20estate%20costs.%20I%20purchased%20my%20apartment%20in%202018%2C%20just%20before%20the%20influx%20of%20other%20Americans%20moving%20in.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20rent%20in%20my%20apartment%20building%20has%20gone%20up%20substantially.%20I've%20seen%20locals%20put%20up%20posters%20around%20the%20neighborhood%20in%20English%20telling%20Americans%20to%20go%20home%20and%20that%20we're%20not%20wanted%20here%20because%20the%20rents%20have%20skyrocketed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20these%20issues%2C%20it's%20better%20to%20stay%20in%20a%20newer%20Airbnb%20or%20stay%20in%20a%20long-term%20hotel%20that's%20licensed%20and%20regulated%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Stop%20raising%20your%20voice%20when%20out%20in%20public%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20noticed%20that%20Mexicans%20are%20very%20polite%20and%20respectful%20so%20if%20you%20raise%20your%20voice%2C%20you%20could%20make%20people%20around%20you%20uncomfortable.%20If%20you're%20upset%2C%20resolve%20your%20issues%20in%20a%20calm%20manner%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-customs-that-are-offensive-abroad-2015-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavoid%20offending%20people%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Stop%20only%20patronizing%20American-owned%20businesses%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20I've%20seen%20many%20new%20bars%20and%20restaurants%20open%20for%20people%20to%20enjoy%2C%20but%20it's%20important%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthentic-mexican-dishes-you-need-to-try-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evisit%20local%20restaurants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20street%20vendors%2C%20and%20supermarkets%20to%20support%20the%20local%20businesses%20around%20you.%20Eating%20in%20the%20streets%20is%20a%20very%20communal%20experience%20here%20and%20it'll%20help%20you%20feel%20more%20accepted%20with%20the%20local%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20moved%20here%2C%20there%20were%20more%20children%20in%20the%20neighborhoods%20along%20with%20more%20parks%20and%20schools.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Ftravel%2Farticle%2F20120403-mexico-citys-ultra-niche-museums%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMexico%20City%20had%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20museums%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20London%20at%20the%20time.%20There%20were%20many%20bookstores%20and%20fondas%20(mom-and-pop%20hotels)%20as%20well.%20After%20the%20recent%20influx%20of%20Americans%2C%20we%20mostly%20have%20restaurants%2C%20bars%2C%20cafes%2C%20boutiques%2C%20and%20clubs.%20I%20don't%20see%20as%20many%20children%20in%20the%20neighborhood%20and%20young%20people%20can't%20afford%20to%20eat%20at%20restaurants%20every%20day%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20in%20the%20summer%2C%20there%20isn't%20enough%20business%20to%20go%20around%20for%20all%20the%20new%20restaurants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Stop%20only%20hanging%20out%20with%20other%20Americans%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMake%20friends%20with%20local%20people%2C%20spend%20time%20with%20them%2C%20and%20take%20the%20time%20to%20learn%20their%20culture.%20I%20make%20it%20a%20point%20to%20hang%20out%20with%20my%20local%20friends%2C%20practice%20my%20Spanish%2C%20and%20learn%20as%20much%20about%20the%20culture%20as%20I%20can.%20I%20regularly%20talk%20to%20my%20neighbors%20and%20the%20vendors%20on%20the%20street.%20This%20helps%20build%20trust%20with%20my%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20neighbors%20have%20known%20me%20for%20years%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraised-bilingual-grateful-family-communication-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20speak%20Spanish%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20interact%20with%20locals%20so%20they%20know%20I'm%20not%20part%20of%20the%20new%20influx%20of%20foreigners%2C%20but%20at%20face%20value%20to%20someone%20walking%20on%20the%20street%2C%20I'd%20definitely%20be%20roped%20into%20the%20group%20of%20gentrifying%20expats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELocals%20can't%20afford%20to%20live%20in%20their%20own%20neighborhoods%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20for%20digital%20nomads%20that%20move%20here%20to%20know%20how%20they're%20affecting%20the%20local%20residents%2C%20culture%2C%20and%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20see%20the%20local%20people%20buying%20food%20from%20the%20street%20vendors%20and%20small%20restaurants%20on%20their%20lunch%20breaks.%20They%20can't%20afford%20to%20do%20that%20anymore.%20Many%20of%20them%20have%20had%20to%20move%20out%20of%20their%20hometowns%20and%20only%20come%20in%20to%20work%20for%20one%20of%20the%20foreigner-run%20businesses%20that%20have%20taken%20over.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-protect-longtime-residents-from-gentrification-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGentrification%20has%20taken%20a%20toll%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20there%20are%20things%20we%20need%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20while%20living%20here%20to%20help%20reduce%20its%20negative%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moving-living-mexico-what-expats-should-stop-doing-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705234441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a19902dcdb354a985745bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moving-living-mexico-what-expats-should-stop-doing-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20American%20moved%20and%20is%20living%20in%20Mexico.%20He%20says%20he%20wants%20newer%20expats%20to%20be%20more%20aware%20of%20things%20they%20can%20do%20to%20stop%20the%20negative%20effects%20of%20gentrification.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ananya%20Vahal)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moving