-as-israel-marks-100th-day-of-hostages-in-captivity%2Famp_articleshow%2F106834247.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Taiwan%3A%20Anti-China%20Leader%20Wins%20Presidential%20Election%2C%20US%20Delegation%20to%20Visit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14145238%2FGDyMc7Ha4AEZDC_.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20unofficial%20delegation%20of%20two%20former%20senior%20US%20officials%20is%20expected%20in%20Taiwan%20on%20Sunday%2C%20a%20day%20after%20Lai%20Ching-te%20from%20the%20ruling%20Democratic%20Progressive%20Party%20(DPP)%20won%20the%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Institute%20in%20Taiwan%20(AIT)%2C%20which%20serves%20as%20the%20de-facto%20US%20embassy%20in%20Taipei%20due%20to%20the%20absence%20of%20official%20diplomatic%20ties%2C%20said%20the%20delegation%20would%20include%20former%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Stephen%20Hadley%20and%20former%20Deputy%20Secretary%20of%20State%20James%20Steinberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELai%20Ching-te%20wins%20Taiwan%20election%20in%20blow%20to%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20we%20have%20done%20previously%20following%20a%20Taiwan%20presidential%20election%2C%20the%20US%20government%20has%20asked%20former%20senior%20officials%20to%20travel%20in%20their%20private%20capacity%20to%20Taiwan%2C%E2%80%9D%20AIT%20said%2C%20adding%20its%20US-based%20Chair%20Laura%20Rosenberger%20would%20join%20the%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20January%2015%2C%20they%20will%20meet%20with%20a%20range%20of%20leading%20political%20figures%20and%20convey%20congratulations%20from%20the%20American%20people%20to%20Taiwan%20on%20its%20successful%20elections%2C%20support%20for%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20continued%20prosperity%20and%20growth%2C%20and%20our%20longstanding%20interest%20in%20cross-Strait%20peace%20and%20stability.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20is%20likely%20to%20irritate%20Beijing%2C%20which%20sees%20the%20island%20as%20part%20of%20China%20and%20has%20vowed%20to%20take%20back%20control%20of%20the%20self-governing%20island%2C%20with%20force%20if%20necessary.%20Similar%20visits%20in%20the%20past%20have%20prompted%20China%20to%20stage%20military%20drills%20in%20apparent%20protest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETaipei%20tells%20Beijing%20to%20%E2%80%98face%20reality%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELai%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20victory%2C%20which%20marks%20a%20continuation%20of%20DPP%20governing%20following%20two%20terms%20under%20his%20predecessor%20Tsai%20Ing-wen%2C%20has%20been%20seen%20as%20a%20rebuff%20to%20China%E2%80%99s%20attempts%20to%20sway%20the%20vote%20in%20favour%20of%20more%20pro-Beijing%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeijing%20has%20previously%20called%20Lai%20a%20dangerous%20separatist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaiwan%E2%80%99s%20Foreign%20Ministry%20called%20on%20Beijing%20to%20accept%20the%20result%20after%20voters%20gave%20Lai%20a%20comfortable%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Ministry%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%20calls%20on%20the%20Beijing%20authorities%20to%20respect%20the%20election%20results%2C%20face%20reality%20and%20give%20up%20suppressing%20Taiwan%20in%20order%20for%20positive%20cross-strait%20interactions%20to%20return%20to%20the%20right%20track%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Beijing%20said%20Lai%E2%80%99s%20victory%20would%20not%20avert%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinevitable%20trend%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20reunification.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20also%20condemned%20a%20statement%20of%20congratulations%20from%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20over%20Lai%E2%80%99s%20win%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cseriously%20incorrect%20signal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CChina%20has%20always%20firmly%20opposed%20any%20form%20of%20official%20exchanges%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Taiwan%2C%20and%20resolutely%20opposes%20the%20United%20States%20interfering%20in%20Taiwan%20affairs%20in%20any%20form%20and%20under%20any%20pretext%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Chinese%20Foreign%20Ministry%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThreat%20of%20conflict%20in%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20main%20trading%20partner%20and%20the%2064-year-old%20Lai%20said%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20work%20with%20Beijing%20to%20maintain%20peace%20and%20stability%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20vowed%20not%20to%20cower%20to%20Chinese%20aggression%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20determined%20to%20safeguard%20Taiwan%20from%20continuing%20threats%20and%20intimidation%20from%20China.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20has%20become%20more%20aggressive%20in%20its%20stance%20toward%20Taiwan%20since%20the%20DPP%20came%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPresident-elect%20Lai%20stands%20for%20%E2%80%98the%20status%20quo%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMilitary%20maneuvers%2C%20including%20both%20Chinese%20ships%20and%20jets%2C%20around%20the%20island%20have%20become%20commonplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rising%20tensions%20have%20sparked%20concern%20about%20the%20prospect%20of%20an%20all-out%20war%20in%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%20which%20would%20have%20global%20impacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficially%2C%20the%20US%20does%20not%20recognize%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20independence.%20However%2C%20while%20Washington%20follows%20the%20%E2%80%9COne%20China%E2%80%9D%20policy%20what%20acknowledges%20Beijing%20as%20the%20sole%20government%20of%20China%2C%20the%20US%20also%20gives%20major%20military%20support%20to%20Taiwan%20and%20opposes%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20assert%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20lead%20to%20Washington%20being%20pulled%20into%20the%20conflict%20in%20case%20Beijing%20decides%20to%20attempt%20a%20military%20takeover%20of%20the%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20report%20first%20appeared%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftaiwan-informal-us-delegation-set-to-visit-after-election%2Fa-67975592%5C%22%3EDW.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705224319000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14145238%2FGDyMc7Ha4AEZDC_.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ftaiwan-anti-china-leader-wins-presidential-election-us-delegation-to-visit%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20move%20is%20likely%20to%20irritate%20Beijing%2C%20which%20sees%20the%20island%20as%20part%20of%20China%20and%20has%20vowed%20to%20take%20back%20control%20of%20the%20self-governing%20island%2C%20with%20force%20if%20necessary.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ftaiwan-anti-china-leader-wins-presidential-election-us-delegation-to-visit%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UN%20Rights%20Experts%20Welcome%20Start%20of%20ICJ%20Genocide%20Hearings%2C%20Reiterate%20Call%20for%20Ceasefire%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14142622%2FGDplfVTW8AEulSK.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESouth%20Africa%20has%20taken%20Israel%20to%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20highest%20court%20and%20told%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20that%20Israel%20was%20perpetrating%20genocide%20in%20Gaza%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-genocidal-south-africa-gaza-irish-lawyer%5C%22%3Ebacking%20up%20its%20claim%20with%20instances%20of%20how%20top%20Israelis%20had%20spoken%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20how%20its%20army%20was%20acting%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20region.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhile%20the%20proceedings%20have%20made%20news%20%E2%80%93%20as%20have%20their%20lack%20of%20airtime%20%E2%80%93%20UN%20human%20rights%20experts%20have%20welcomed%20the%20move.%20The%20full%20press%20release%20of%20this%20is%20produced%20below.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUN%20human%20rights%20experts*%20today%20welcomed%20the%20start%20of%20hearings%20before%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20(%E2%80%9CICJ%E2%80%9D)%20of%20a%20case%20brought%20by%20South%20Africa%20concerning%20allegations%20that%20Israel%20is%20committing%20acts%20of%20genocide%20against%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%20The%20experts%20emphasized%20that%20any%20decision%20the%20Court%20reaches%20on%20provisional%20measures%20must%20be%20respected%20and%20implemented%20by%20the%20parties%20to%20the%20dispute%2C%20as%20required%20by%20the%20ICJ%20Statute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Africa%20on%2029%20December%202023%20asked%20the%20ICJ%20to%20urgently%20issue%20provisional%20measures%20ordering%20Israel%20to%20immediately%20suspend%20its%20military%20operations%20in%20and%20against%20Gaza%20and%20to%20protect%20residents%20from%20acts%20of%20genocide%2C%20alleging%20breaches%20by%20Israel%20of%20the%201948%20Convention%20on%20the%20Prevention%20and%20Punishment%20of%20the%20Crime%20of%20Genocide%20(the%20%E2%80%9CGenocide%20Convention%E2%80%9D).%20The%20Genocide%20Convention%20defines%20genocide%20as%20%E2%80%9Cacts%20committed%20with%20intent%20to%20destroy%2C%20in%20whole%20or%20in%20part%2C%20a%20national%2C%20ethnical%2C%20racial%20or%20religious%20group%E2%80%9D.%20The%20hearings%20concerning%20the%20request%20for%20provisional%20measures%20will%20be%20held%20on%2011%20and%2012%20January%20at%20The%20Hague%2C%20in%20The%20Netherlands.%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20filing%20also%20alleges%20that%20Israel%20is%20inciting%20genocide%20and%20has%20failed%20to%20prevent%20genocide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CICJ%20decisions%20are%20final%2C%20binding%2C%20and%20not%20subject%20to%20appeal.%20Adherence%20to%20any%20order%20the%20Court%20may%20make%20by%20the%20parties%20involved%20is%20imperative%20for%20protecting%20the%20rights%20of%20Palestinians%20and%20reinforcing%20the%20primacy%20of%20international%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20commend%20South%20Africa%20for%20bringing%20this%20case%20to%20the%20ICJ%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20rights%20of%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20are%20being%20violated%20with%20impunity.%20We%20call%20on%20all%20States%20to%20cooperate%20with%20the%20Court%20as%20it%20interprets%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%20and%20to%20respect%20the%20role%20of%20the%20ICJ%20as%20an%20independent%20court%20of%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experts%20also%20welcomed%20the%20statements%20of%20support%20by%20many%20States%20for%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20action%20in%20bringing%20the%20case%20to%20the%20Court%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20principled%20stand%20taken%20by%20individuals%20and%20organizations%20worldwide%20that%20have%20expressed%20support%20for%20the%20submission%20of%20the%20case%20by%20South%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experts%20noted%20that%20this%20is%20not%20the%20first%20such%20case.%20In%202019%2C%20for%20example%2C%20The%20Gambia%20brought%20a%20case%20against%20Myanmar%20under%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%20to%20the%20ICJ%2C%20and%20asked%20for%20the%20Court%20to%20issue%20provisional%20measures%20calling%20for%20a%20halt%20to%20atrocities%20against%20the%20Rohingya%20people.%20The%20Court%20issued%20provisional%20measures%20in%20that%20case%2C%20which%20is%20still%20pending%20determination%20before%20the%20ICJ.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20South%20Africa%20and%20Israel%20have%20ratified%20the%201948%20Convention%20on%20the%20Prevention%20and%20Punishment%20of%20the%20Crime%20of%20Genocide%2C%20as%20have%20151%20other%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSouth%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20has%20broader%20implications%20for%20all%20States%20%E2%80%93%20not%20only%20those%20that%20have%20ratified%20the%20Convention%20%E2%80%93%20as%20all%20are%20obligated%20both%20to%20refrain%20from%20committing%20genocide%2C%20and%20to%20prevent%20and%20punish%20it%20wherever%20it%20occurs.%20All%20States%20must%20act%20together%20to%20prevent%2C%20halt%2C%20and%20punish%20genocide%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20ICJ%20has%20in%20the%20past%20made%20clear%20that%20obligations%20under%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%20are%20of%20an%C2%A0erga%20omnes%C2%A0nature%2C%20meaning%20that%20any%20and%20all%20countries%20have%20a%20stake%20in%20preventing%20genocide%20wherever%20it%20is%20at%20risk%20of%20occurring.%20This%20plainly%20means%20that%20uninvolved%20countries%20have%20standing%20to%20bring%20a%20case%20like%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20to%20the%20ICJ%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20experts%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20application%20to%20the%20Court%2C%20South%20Africa%20cited%20numerous%20statements%20by%20UN%20Special%20Procedures%20mandate%20holders%2C%20including%20the%20experts%E2%80%99%20repeated%20calls%20for%20international%20action%20to%20prevent%20genocide%20in%20Gaza.%20The%20mandate%20holders%E2%80%99%20statements%20reference%20evidence%20of%20genocidal%20incitement%20by%20Israeli%20Government%20officials%2C%20including%20a%20stated%20intent%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdestroy%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20under%20occupation%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20calls%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Csecond%20Nakba%E2%80%9D%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20occupied%20Palestinian%20territory.%20These%20comments%20by%20Israeli%20officials%20have%20been%20made%20amidst%20the%20extensive%20use%20by%20Israel%20of%20powerful%2C%20often%20unguided%20weaponry%20in%20Gaza%20with%20inherently%20indiscriminate%20impacts%2C%20severe%20restrictions%20on%20the%20entry%20of%20lifesaving%20humanitarian%20aid%2C%20and%20attacks%20on%20health%20care%20services%2C%20all%20of%20which%20have%20resulted%20in%20a%20devastating%20death%20toll%2C%20including%20large%20numbers%20of%20women%20and%20children%2C%20the%20forcible%20transfer%20of%20more%20than%20half%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20and%20extensive%20destruction%20of%20life-sustaining%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20the%20alarming%20magnitude%20and%20intensity%20of%20the%20bombardments%2C%20the%20experts%20also%20reiterated%20their%20demand%2C%20issued%20in%20December%202023%20along%20with%20other%20Special%20Procedure%20mandate%20holders%2C%20for%20an%20immediate%20ceasefire%20and%20a%20halt%20to%20displacement%2C%20domicide%2C%20and%20attacks%20on%20health%20infrastructure.%20The%20experts%20further%20called%20for%20immediate%20action%20to%20ensure%20the%20unimpeded%20delivery%20of%20desperately%20needed%20humanitarian%20aid%20to%20people%20in%20Gaza%2C%20especially%20for%20the%20sick%20or%20injured%2C%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20older%20persons%2C%20pregnant%20women%2C%20and%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*The%20experts%3A%C2%A0Ms.%20Margaret%20Satterthwaite%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fsr-independence-of-judges-and-lawyers%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fsr-independence-of-judges-and-lawyers%5C%22%3ESpecial%20Rapporteur%20on%20the%20independence%20of%20judges%20and%20lawyers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0Ms.%20Francesca%20Albanese%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fsr-palestine%5C%22%3ESpecial%20Rapporteur%20on%20the%20situation%20of%20human%20rights%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20Territory%20occupied%20since%201967%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0Ms.%20Siobh%C3%A1n%20Mullally%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fsr-trafficking-in-persons%5C%22%3ESpecial%20Rapporteur%20on%20trafficking%20in%20persons%2C%20especially%20women%20and%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fspecial-procedures%2Fsr-slavery%2Fannual-thematic-reports%5C%22%3ETomoya%20Obokata%2C%C2%A0Special%20Rapporteur%20on%20contemporary%20forms%20of%20slavery%2C%20including%20its%20causes%