%20politics%20in%20India%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20serious%20anthropologist%20or%20historian%20of%20India%20can%20claim%20to%20have%20decisively%20answered%20the%20following%20basic%20question%3A%20why%20has%20caste%20%E2%80%93%20as%20an%20ideology%2C%20a%20social%20formation%20and%20a%20cosmology%20%E2%80%93%20spread%20and%20survived%20over%20two%20millennia%20or%20more%20without%20any%20sort%20of%20central%20political%20authority%2C%20bureaucracy%20or%20continental%20religious%20organisation%20of%20priests%2C%20monks%20or%20clerical%20staff%3F%20The%20spread%20and%20persistence%20of%20this%20unique%20form%20of%20racial%2C%20ethnic%20and%20economic%20stratification%20has%20been%20studied%20in%20all%20its%20avatars%2C%20variations%20and%20disguises%20but%20its%20remarkable%20region-wide%20tenacity%20has%20not%20yet%20been%20accounted%20for%20adequately.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20subject%20of%20what%20motivates%20an%20electorate%20to%20emotively%20vote%20for%20one%20party%20against%20another%2C%20despite%20facing%20strong%20economic%20adversities%20and%20socio-economic%20challenges%2C%20remains%20still%20understudied%20and%20undervalued%20(being%20restricted%20to%20a%20few%20disciplines%20and%20its%20practitioners).%20And%2C%20a%20lack%20of%20knowledge%20cost%20attached%20to%20it%20imposes%20the%20most%20serious%20adverse%20consequences%20for%20any%20developing%20nation%20in%20its%20(future)%20development%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20really%20matters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20at%20this%20point%2C%20two%20pressing%20issues%20strike%20out%3A%20rising%20income%20%26amp%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjgu.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com%2Fjslh%2FAccess(In)Equality%2BIndex%2BReport%2B2021.pdf%5C%22%3Eaccess%20inequality%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20rising%20gap%20between%20output-employment%20creation%20for%20millions%20of%20(aspiring)%20workers%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13171815%2Fimage-1741.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22940%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13171815%2Fimage-1741.png%20940w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13171815%2Fimage-1741-300x216.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692831%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22678%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20look%20at%20the%20income%20growth%20by%20income%20group%20from%202016%20to%202021%20in%20India%2C%20the%20top%2020%25%20rich%20have%20seen%20almost%20a%2040%25%20rise%20in%20their%20income%20growth%20while%20the%20middle%2020%25%2C%20lower%20middle%2020%25%20and%20poorest%2020%25%20have%20all%20seen%20a%20negative%20income%20growth.%20This%20explains%20how%20rising%20income%20inequality%20has%20exploded%20in%20the%20last%20six%20to%20seven%20years%20under%20the%20Modi%20government%20era%20of%20economic%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20even%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fdeepanshu-mohan-richa-sekhani-latika-sharma-advait%5C%22%3Eaccess%20equality%3C%2Fa%3E%20standpoint%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fdeepanshu-mohan-richa-sekhani-latika-sharma-advait%5C%22%3Eas%20studied%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20explained%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20assessing%20how%20Indian%20states%20can%20be%20measured%20in%20terms%20of%20ensuring%20%E2%80%98access%E2%80%99%20to%20basic%20social%2C%20economic%20public%20goods%20(education%2C%20healthcare%2C%20social%20security%2C%20legal%20recourse%2C%20finance)%20the%20actual%20situation%20for%20most%20Indians%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20worse%2C%20which%2C%20when%20combined%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findia-inflationary-tax-poor-corporate-greed-price-gouging%5C%22%3Ea%20rising%20inflationary%20tax%20guided%20by%20colluding%20corporate%20greed%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20instances%20of%20price%20gouging%20(backed%20by%20government%20support)%20is%20eroding%20the%20way%20of%20life%20and%20standard%20of%20living%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98poor%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98low-income%E2%80%99%20class%20as%20a%20whole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20look%20at%20output-employment%20growth%20over%20the%20last%20six%20to%20seven%20years%2C%20particularly%20from%20the%20post-demonetisation%20(2016)%20period%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20sharp%20fall%20in%20the%20overall%20output%20(if%20we%20only%20look%20at%20industrial%20production%20levels)%20and%20in%20the%20aggregate%20employment%20rate%20of%20the%20eligible%20job-seeking%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gendered%20effects%20of%20these%20trends%20are%20even%20more%20striking%2C%20where%20the%20female%20employment%20rate%20has%20dropped%20from%2011.88%25%20(2016-17)%20to%207.96%25%20(2021-22).%20In%20urban%20areas%2C%20for%20women%2C%20the%20employment%20rate%20has%20dropped%20from%2010.77%25%20t0%205.57%25%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13172133%2Fimage-1742.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22940%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13172133%2Fimage-1742.png%20940w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13172133%2Fimage-1742-300x200.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692832%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22627%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13172548%2Fimage-1744.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22940%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13172548%2Fimage-1744.png%20940w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13172548%2Fimage-1744-300x75.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692833%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22236%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20CMIE%20Employment%20Data%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20anyone%20looks%20at%20these%20three%20charts%20with%20other%20cumulative%20set%20of%20data%20points%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20acknowledge%2C%20or%20ascertain%2C%20how%20a%20party%2C%20such%20as%20the%20BJP%2C%20under%20Modi%2C%20which%20has%20actually%20done%20very%20little%20for%20the%20middle%20class%20(in%20terms%20of%20creating%20new%20jobs%20and%20income%20mobility%20opportunities)%2C%20further%20added%20to%20the%20growing%20inequality%20amidst%20rising%20prices%2C%20making%20the%20%E2%80%98poor%E2%80%99%20more%20vulnerable%2C%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20a%20growing%20narrow%20class%20of%20elites%20(usurping%20greater%20financial%2C%20corporate%20and%20money%20control)%2C%20has%20continued%20to%20remain%20electorally%20%E2%80%98popular%E2%80%99%2C%20while%20garnering%20more%20electoral%20votes%20from%20the%20very%20states%20(like%20UP%2C%20MP%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20etc.)%20where%20these%20economic%20data%20trends%20signal%20their%20worst%20position%20(as%20compared%20to%202014).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%2C%20as%20the%20face%20of%20the%20political%20opposition%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20being%20aware%20of%20this%2C%20has%20done%20very%20little%20to%20either%20capture%20the%20imagination%20of%20the%20electorate%20on%20the%20issues%20of%20jobs%2C%20inequality%2C%20price%20rise%2C%20etc%2C%20while%20suffering%20acutely%20from%20a%20crisis%20of%20a%20visionary%20leadership%2C%20and%20organisational%20incompetence%20(when%20compared%20to%20the%20BJP)%20that%20can%20present%20a%20powerful%20counter%20narrative%20to%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20Bharat%20Yatra%2C%20unless%20secured%20and%20guided%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftrucker-protests-are-another-instance-of-the-success-of-street-politics%5C%22%3Ea%20people%E2%80%99s%20movement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20anchored%20by%20a%20leader%20whose%20voice%20and%20presence%20closely%20resonates%20with%20the%20anguish%20of%20those%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20will%20be%20able%20to%20shift%20voter%20preference%20in%202024%2C%20in%20favour%20of%20one%20party%20(BJP)%20as%20against%20the%20other%20(Congress).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20perhaps%20needed%20by%20a%20political%20opposition%20is%20a%20cohesive%20vision%2C%20backed%20by%20an%20even%20more%20inspiring%20leadership%20that%20brings%20forth%20a%20powerful%20counter-punch%20to%20the%20BJP%20trying%20to%20build%20itself%20on%20a%20long%20term%20theory%20of%20driving%20socio-economic%20change.%20It%E2%80%99s%20about%20time%20how%20that%20%E2%80%98vision%E2%80%99%20is%20realised%20by%20a%20political%20opposition%20which%20has%20so%20far%20failed%20to%20capture%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20attention%20(particularly%20in%20key%20north%20Indian%20and%20western%20states)%2C%20against%20a%20party%20(and%20its%20leader)%20drunk%20on%20a%20brutish%20exhibition%20of%20power%2C%20religious%20majoritarianism%2C%20abdicating%20all%20basic%20features%20of%20constitutional%20and%20civic%20morality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20economics%20and%20director%2C%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20OP%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705199423000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F17172239%2FSupporter_of_Bharati