2021-22%2C%20the%20average%20monthly%20earnings%20of%20a%20regular%20salaried%20man%20was%20approximately%20Rs.%2017%2C910.%20A%20salaried%20woman%20earned%20about%20Rs.%2013%2C666.%20In%20casual%20wage%20work%2C%20the%20earnings%20disparity%20was%20higher%2C%20with%20women%20earning%20only%2060%25%20of%20what%20men%20earn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20the%20share%20of%20women%20in%20self-employment%20has%20remained%20stagnant%20over%20most%20of%20the%20post-reform%20period%20(and%20has%20even%20increased%20during%20the%20Covid%20and%20post-Covid%20period).%20This%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20concern%20because%20the%20earnings%20gap%20is%20highest%20in%20the%20case%20of%20self-employment%2C%20with%20women%2C%20on%20average%2C%20earning%20only%2040%25%20of%20men%E2%80%99s%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190006%2FRatios.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22609%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190006%2FRatios.png%20609w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190006%2FRatios-300x138.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692848%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22280%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETable%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20these%20disparities%20play%20out%20across%20the%20earnings%20distribution%3F%20As%20women%20move%20up%20the%20earnings%20ladder%2C%20are%20they%20earning%20closer%20to%20what%20men%20make%20or%20does%20the%20gap%20widen%20even%20further%3F%20Figure%201%20(below)%20gives%20us%20an%20answer%20to%20this%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20each%20type%20of%20employment%2C%20we%20divide%20the%20earnings%20into%20ten%20groups%20representing%20the%20lowest%20(decile%201)%20and%20highest%20earners%20(decile%2010).%20As%20we%20see%20in%20Table%201%2C%20across%20the%20earnings%20distribution%2C%20self-employment%20has%20the%20highest%20gender-based%20earnings%20gap.%20By%20contrast%2C%20salaried%20employment%20has%20a%20much%20lower%20earnings%20gap%20and%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20this%20gap%20steadily%20narrows%20as%20one%20moves%20up%20the%20earnings%20distribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20top%20of%20the%20salaried%20earnings%20spectrum%2C%20women%20earn%2090%25%20of%20what%20men%20earn%2C%20on%20average.%20For%20self-employment%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20earnings%20gap%20is%20still%20high%2C%20with%20women%20earning%20around%2060%25%20of%20what%20men%20make.%20Although%20the%20gender%20earnings%20gap%20in%20self-employment%20narrows%20as%20one%20moves%20up%20the%20earnings%20distribution%2C%20it%20remains%20quite%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190515%2FRatios-by-decile.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22808%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190515%2FRatios-by-decile.png%20808w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190515%2FRatios-by-decile-300x214.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692850%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22577%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChart%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrends%20in%20earnings%20gap%20over%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficial%20estimates%20of%20earnings%20from%20self-employment%20have%20only%20been%20collected%20since%202017%2C%20whereas%20we%20have%20information%20on%20wage%20earnings%20from%20the%201980s%20onwards.%20Figure%202%20shows%20the%20long%20run%20trends%20in%20earnings%20gap%20for%20salaried%20workers%20within%20each%20quartile%20group%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190830%2FRatios-per-quartile-and-time.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22835%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190830%2FRatios-per-quartile-and-time.png%20835w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190830%2FRatios-per-quartile-and-time-300x210.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692851%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22585%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChart%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExplaining%20the%20trends%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20over%20time%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20narrowing%20of%20the%20earnings%20gap%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20second%20and%20third%20quartiles.%20Two%20possibilities%20can%20explain%20this%20narrowing%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%2C%20gender-based%20discrimination%20in%20the%20labour%20market%20may%20have%20decreased%20over%20time%2C%20with%20employers%20treating%20men%20and%20women%20similarly.%20Or%20it%20could%20be%20that%20the%20very%20nature%20of%20women%20participating%20in%20the%20labour%20market%20(vis-a-vis%20men)%20has%20changed%2C%20with%20more%20educational%20attainment%20among%20women%20as%20well%20as%20an%20improvement%20in%20the%20kinds%20of%20occupations%20and%20industries%20they%20had%20access%20to%20within%20regular%20salaried%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20over%20this%20period%2C%20a%20large%20change%20has%20occurred%20in%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20female%20workforce.%20Older%2C%20less%20educated%20women%20have%20exited%20while%20younger%2C%20more%20educated%20women%20have%20entered.%20Fewer%20women%20are%20employed%20in%20agriculture%20and%20more%20and%20more%20women%20are%20in%20the%20services%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpandemic-exacerbated-identity-based-discrimination-india-labour-market%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20Pandemic%20Exacerbated%20Identity-Based%20Discrimination%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20Labour%20Market%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20discern%20how%20much%20these%20compositional%20changes%20explain%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20earnings%20gap%20over%20time%2C%20we%20use%20a%20standard%20decomposition%20technique.%20The%20Kitagawa-Oaxaca-Blinder%20decomposition%20considers%20the%20average%20earnings%20difference%20between%20men%20and%20women%20and%20identifies%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20this%20difference%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20%E2%80%9Cexplained%20differences%E2%80%9D%2C%20i.e.%2C%20differences%20in%20observable%20characteristics%20between%20the%20two%20groups%2C%20and%20to%20%E2%80%9Cunexplained%20differences%E2%80%9D%2C%20i.e.%2C%20differences%20in%20unobservable%20characteristics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObservable%20characteristics%20include%20education%2C%20marital%20status%2C%20number%20of%20children%2C%20industry%2C%20and%20occupation%20of%20employment.%20The%20unobservable%20component%20is%20often%20interpreted%20as%20measuring%20discrimination%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20include%20the%20effect%20of%20omitted%20characteristics%20for%20which%20data%20is%20not%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETable%202%20shows%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20explained%20and%20unexplained%20components%20over%20time.%20From%201983%20onward%2C%20there%20is%20a%20steady%20decline%20in%20the%20explained%20component.%20This%20reflects%20how%20the%20characteristics%20of%20men%20and%20women%20in%20the%20labour%20market%20have%2C%20over%20time%2C%20become%20similar%20and%2C%20hence%2C%20explain%20less%20and%20less%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%202021-22%2C%20about%2080%25%20of%20the%20earnings%20gap%20is%20attributable%20to%20this%20unexplained%20component.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13191854%2FOaxaca.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22876%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13191854%2FOaxaca.png%20876w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13191854%2FOaxaca-300x143.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692853%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22417%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETable%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20increase%20is%20more%20dramatic%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20rural%20workforce%2C%20where%20more%20than%2090%25%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap%20in%202021-22%20was%20not%20explained%20by%20workers%E2%80%99%20characteristics.%20But%20the%20period%20that%20saw%20a%20rapid%20rise%20in%20the%20female%20salaried%20workforce%20(1999%20to%202017)%20did%20also%20see%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20unexplained%20component%20in%20urban%20India%20as%20well.%20Thus%2C%20the%20finding%20is%20a%20general%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20size%20of%20the%20gap%20itself%20increased%20substantially%20in%20rural%20India%20but%20the%20increase%20is%20much%20less%20pronounced%20in%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20larger%20conclusion%20is%20worth%20emphasising.%20The%20same%20period%20that%20saw%20a%20rapid%20rise%20in%20regular%20wage%20work%20among%20women%20also%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20unexplained%20part%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap%2C%20usually%20attributed%20to%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20two%20decades%20have%20seen%20a%20large%20churn%20in%20the%20Indian%20female%20workforce.%20The%20increase%20in%20the%20share%20of%20women%20as%20salaried%20workers%20is%20good%20news.%20However%2C%20this%20increase%20has%20not%20led%20to%20a%20systematic%20reduction%20in%20the%20unexplained%20earnings%20gap.%20Rather%2C%20educational%20convergence%20has%20revealed%20the%20potential%20role%20of%20discrimination%20in%20causing%20the%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20an%20increase%20in%20education%20and%20improved%20access%20to%20non-agricultural%20employment%2C%20women%20continue%20to%20earn%20less%20than%20men.%20But%20once%20again%2C%20it%20is%20encouraging%20that%2C%20as%20one%20moves%20up%20the%20earnings%20ladder%2C%20the%20gap%20reduces%2C%20which%20may%20reflect%20less%20discriminatory%20conditions%20for%20women%20in%20relatively%20more%20formal%20parts%20of%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20policy%20responses%20that%20encourage%20improved%20access%20to%20education%20for%20girls%20and%20enable%20the%20expansion%20of%20formal%20employment%20can%20help%20narrow%20the%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAmit%20Basole%20and%20Rosa%20Abraham%20are%20faculty%20at%20Azim%20Premji%20University.%20The%20analysis%20presented%20here%20was%20assisted%20by%20Hami%20Ameen%2C%20Research%20Associate%20at%20Azim%20Premji%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20originally%20appeared%20in%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%5C%22%3EIndia%20in%20Transition%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20publication%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%E2%80%99s%20Center%20for%20the%20Advanced%20Study%20of%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705156416000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13200128%2FWorkplace.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fdiscrimination-gender-wage-gap-casi-sas%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20same%20period%20that%20saw%20a%20rapid%20rise%20in%20regular%20wage%20work%20among%20women%20also%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98unexplained%E2%80%99%20part%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap%2C%20which%20is%20usually%20attributed%20to%20discrimination.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fdiscrimination-gender-wage-gap-casi-sas%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kashmir%20Is%20Hotter%20Than%20New%20Delhi%20This%20Winter.%20Here's%20What%20This%20Means%20for%20Its%20Tourism%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13090719%2Fe754ad51-2fd3-4e9e-9c75-503ea47d968c-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20harshest%20winter%20period%20called%20%E2%80%98Chilai%20Kalan%E2%80%99%2C%20Kashmir%20Valley%20is%20witnessing%20a%20prolonged%20spell%20of%20dry%20weather%20and%20bright%20sunshine%20with%20temperature%20rising%20above%20the%20levels%20recorded%20in%20New%20Delhi%20and%20other%20prominent%20cities%20in%20north%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EKashmir%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWeather%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20an%20independent%20weather%20forecaster%2C%20Srinagar%2C%20the%20summer%20capital%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20recorded%2014.2%C2%B0%20Celsius%20temperature%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20January%209%2C%20which%20was%20eight%20notches%20above%20average%20at%20this%20time%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Delhi%2C%20Chandigarh%2C%20Amritsar%2C%20and%20Ludhiana%2C%20the%20maximum%20temperatures%C2%A0%20were%2013.4%C2%B0%20Celsius%2C%2010.5%C2%B0%20Celsius%2C%209.5%C2%B0%20Celsius%20and%2010.6%C2%B0%20Celsius%2C%E2%80%9D%20Faizan%20Arif%2C%20who%20runs%20the%20weather%20channel%20on%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChilai%20Kalan%2C%20the%2040-day%20winter%20period%20which%20starts%20in%20Kashmir%20on%20December%2021%2C%20is%20marked%20by%20incessant%20snowfall%20and%20subzero%20temperature%20that%20causes%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20inconvenience%20to%20the%20residents%20who%20often%20wake%20up%20in%20the%20morning%20to%20the%20sight%20of%20frozen%20drinking%20water%20taps%20and%20no%20electricity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIrfan%20Rashid%2C%20a%20faculty%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Geoinformatics%2C%20University%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20said%20that%20the%20Valley%20is%20witnessing%20snowless%20winter%20after%20seven%20years%2C%20which%20will%20have%20a%20cascading%20effect%20on%20the%20generation%20capacity%20of%20hydropower%20projects%2C%20agriculture%20activities%20and%20winter%20tourism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERashid%20warned%20that%20in%20case%20the%20dry%20spell%20continued%2C%20it%20would%20lead%20to%20%E2%80%9Chigher%20mass%20loss%20of%20glaciers%E2%80%9D%20which%20will%20not%20only%20impact%20the%20flow%20of%20water%20in%20the%20streams%20and%20rivers%20of%20Kashmir%20during%20the%20summers%20but%20also%20have%20long-term%20effect%20on%20the%20Himalayan%20ecosystems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJhelum%20river%2C%20the%20major%20source%20of%20irrigation%20in%20Kashmir%20which%20bisects%20the%20Srinagar%20city%2C%20ran%20at%20historic%20low%20level%20in%20September%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13090739%2FIMG_3744.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13090739%2FIMG_3744.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13090739%2FIMG_3744-300x124.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13090739%2FIMG_3744-1024x424.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692773%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22497%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Srinagar%20station%20of%20Indian%20Meteorological%20Department%2C%20December%20recorded%20an%20unprecedented%2079%20percent%20deficit%20of%20rainfall%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20with%20the%20overall%20precipitation%20witnessing%20a%20seven%20percent%20deficit%20in%202023%20which%20was%20marked%20by%20interplays%20of%20extreme%20weather%20between%20intense%20heat%20waves%20and%20extreme%20precipitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20peer-reviewed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs10661-013-3559-7%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20titled%20%E2%80%98Sustainability%20of%20winter%20tourism%20in%20a%20changing%20climate%20over%20Kashmir%20Himalaya%E2%80%99%20in%20%3Cem%3ESpringer%3C%2Fem%3E%20magazine%20observed%20that%20there%20has%20been%20a%20decreased%20precipitation%20in%20Kashmir%20from%20the%20past%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CImplications%20of%20climate%20change%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20less%20snow%2C%20receding%20glaciers%2C%20increasing%20temperatures%2C%20and%20decreasing%20precipitation.%20Climate%20change%20is%20also%20a%20severe%20threat%20to%20snow-related%20winter%20sports%20such%20as%20skiing%2C%20snowboarding%2C%20and%20cross-country%20skiing%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20study%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20north%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20hill%20resort%20of%20Gulmarg%2C%20which%20used%20to%20be%20covered%20under%20snow%20at%20this%20time%20of%20the%20year%2C%20hues%20of%20gold%20and%20crimson%20coloured%20grass%20welcome%20the%20tourists.%20Due%20to%20lack%20of%20snow%2C%20winter%20sports%20activities%20such%20as%20snowboarding%20and%20skiing%20at%20the%20hill%20resort%20have%20taken%20a%20backseat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUnfortunately%2C%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20the%20best%20of%20news%20for%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Brian%20Newman%2C%20who%20works%20with%20Gulmarg%20Ski%20Patrol%20and%20Avalanche%20Centre%2C%20%E2%80%9COn%20average%2C%20there%20is%2050-70%20cm%20of%20snow%20at%204000%20metres%20which%20fell%20on%20December%2010.%20Without%20any%20new%20snow%2C%20we%20have%20insufficient%20snowpack%20to%20open%20the%20ski%20area%20as%20yet.%20The%20bad%20news%20is%20that%20there%20is%20no%20forecast%20of%20snow%20for%20next%20week.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20study%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS1470160X21003551%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EScience%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EDirect%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20noted%20that%20the%20average%20annual%20mean%20maximum%20temperature%20in%20Kashmir%20increased%20by%20two%20notches%20between%201980%20to%202020%2C%20an%20increase%20of%200.5%C2%B0%20Celsius%20per%20decade%20which%20is%20far%20more%20than%200.2%20degree%20Celsius%20increase%20recorded%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarhat%20Naik%2C%20a%20national-level%20snowboarder%20from%20Tangmarg%20area%20of%20north%20Kashmir%2C%20said%20that%20the%20bowl%20of%20Gulmarg%20is%20witnessing%20an%20unprecedented%20flower%20bloom%20which%20usually%20happened%20at%20the%20onset%20of%20spring%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20shocking%20to%20say%20the%20least%2C%E2%80%9D%20Naik%2C%20who%20also%20coordinates%20the%20National%20Winter%20Games%20which%20are%20held%20in%20Gulmarg.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaik%2C%20a%20snowboarding%20instructor%2C%20said%20that%20the%20deficit%20in%20snowfall%20has%20adversely%20impacted%20the%20winter%20tourism%20economy%20of%20Gulmarg.%20The%20fate%20of%20the%20National%20Winter%20Games%2C%20which%20are%20held%20in%20Gulmarg%20in%20the%20first%20week%20of%20February%2C%20also%20hangs%20in%20the%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20lack%20of%20snowfall%20has%20also%20affected%20the%20preparations%20of%20sportspersons%20like%20skiers%20and%20snowboarders%20who%20haven%E2%80%99t%20been%20able%20to%20hit%20the%20slopes%2C%E2%80%9D%20Naik%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dry%20spell%20has%20also%20led%20to%20the%20cancellation%20of%20hotel%20bookings%2C%20especially%20in%20Gulmarg%20which%20used%20to%20be%20thronged%20by%20tourists%20in%20winter.%20Mohammad%20Shafi%2C%20an%20official%20with%20Jammu%20Kashmir%20Tourism%20Development%20Corporation%2C%20said%20that%20the%20occupancy%20of%20hotels%20in%20Gulmarg%20has%20shrunk%20by%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13090709%2FIMG_3753.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13090709%2FIMG_3753.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13090709%2FIMG_3753-300x225.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692770%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESpring%20flowers%20blooming%20on%20the%20meadows%20of%20Gulmarg%20due%20to%20extreme%20weather%20conditions%20prevailing%20in%20Kashmir.%20Photo%3A%20By%20special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTourists%20are%20not%20coming%20to%20Kashmir%20these%20days.%20There%20have%20been%20hundreds%20of%20cancellations%20of%20hotel%20bookings%20as%20there%20has%20been%20no%20snowfall%20this%20year%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Mushtaq%20Chaya%2C%20one%20of%20the%20leading%20hoteliers%20from%20Kashmir%20whose%20properties%20are%20located%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManzoor%20Ahmad%20Pakhtoon%2C%20President%20of%20Kashmir%20Houseboat%20Association%20said%20that%20the%20tourism%20industry%20has%20suffered%20badly%20due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20precipitation%20this%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHouseboats%20are%20an%20essential%20part%20of%20the%20itinerary%20of%20tourists%20visiting%20the%20Valley%20but%20these%20days%20many%20of%20them%20are%20stranded%20on%20mud%20cakes%20along%20the%20parched%20banks%20of%20Jehlum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20lot%20of%20bookings%20are%20getting%20cancelled.%20While%20the%20houseboats%20registered%2060-70%20percent%20occupancy%20last%20year%2C%20it%20has%20fallen%20to%2020-25%20percent%20this%20year%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Pakhtoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20special%20prayer%20called%20%E2%80%98Salatul%20Istisqa%E2%80%99%20was%20offered%20at%20Jamia%20Masjid%20in%20Srinagar%20on%20Friday%20to%20seek%20divine%20intervention%20in%20ending%20the%20prevailing%20dry%20weather%20conditions%20in%20Kashmir.%20According%20to%20reports%2C%20a%20large%20number%20of%20devotees%20participated%20in%20the%20prayers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deficit%20in%20precipitation%20has%20also%20shadowed%20the%20generation%20capacity%20of%20hydroelectricity%20projects%20in%20Kashmir%20Valley%20which%20is%20reeling%20under%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20power%20crises%20in%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20subzero%20temperatures%2C%20the%20water%20flow%20from%20the%20glaciers%20and%20alpine%20lakes%20in%20the%20higher%20reaches%20has%20decreased%20significantly%2C%20which%20has%20reduced%20generation%20by%20around%2070%20percent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDue%20to%20high%20demand%20of%20electricity%20in%20winters%2C%20the%20situation%20will%20worsen%20if%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20precipitation%20in%20Kashmir%20in%20coming%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20an%20official%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Power%20Development%20Corporation%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20be%20named.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKashmir%E2%80%99s%20dry%20weather%20conditions%20have%20also%20led%20to%20an%20explosion%20of%20seasonal%20illnesses.%20Dr%20Muhammad%20Saleem%20Khan%2C%20who%20heads%20the%20Department%20of%20Community%20Medicine%20at%20SMHS%20Hospital%20in%20Srinagar%20said%20that%20the%20viral%20infections%20and%20other%20seasonal%20illnesses%20increase%20due%20to%20dry%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705152649000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13090719%2Fe754ad51-2fd3-4e9e-9c75-503ea47d968c-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftravel%2Fkashmir-is-hotter-than-new-delhi-this-winter-heres-what-this-means-for-its-tourism%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20dry%20spell%20has%20led%20to%20cancellation%20of%20hotel%20bookings%2C%20especially%20in%20Gulmarg%20which%20used%20to%20be%20thronged%20by%20tourists%20in%20winter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A82%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftravel%2Fkashmir-is-hotter-than-new-delhi-this-winter-heres-what-this-means-for-its-tourism%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Uddhav%20Thackeray%20Invites%20President%20to%20Ram%20Function%20in%20Nashik%20on%20Same%20Day%20as%20Ayodhya%20Consecration%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F28221655%2FScreenshot-2022-06-28-at-10.16.11-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Shiv%20Sena%20(UBT)%20leader%20Uddhav%20Thackeray%20appealed%20to%20President%20Droupadi%20Murmu%20to%20attend%20a%20religious%20function%20scheduled%20at%20Nashik%E2%80%99s%20Kalaram%20Temple%20on%20January%2022%2C%20saying%20it%20would%20%E2%80%9Cenhance%20the%20dignity%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20consecration%20of%20the%20Ayodhya%20Ram%20Temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20letter%20dated%20Friday%20(January%2012)%2C%20Thackeray%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2Fmumbai%2Fuddhav-thackeray-to-perform-maha-aarti-on-january-22-at-nashiks-kalaram-temple%2Farticle67713500.ece%5C%22%3Ewho%20was%20not%20invited%20to%20the%20Ayodhya%20event%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20also%20slated%20for%20January%2022%20%E2%80%93%20referred%20